// Semantic direction:
// feil_domene is the top-level module organizing all error types and their relationships.
// feil_årsak_kjede links errors causally: each feil can wrap a previous feil as its årsak.
// feil_kontekst_kjede attaches diagnostic context strings at each layer without altering the type.
// strukturert_feil carries machine-readable feil_kode plus human-readable message and metadata.
// feil_kategori enables cross-cutting error handling without matching every specific type.
// alvorlighetsgrad_gjenforsøkbar marks errors that may succeed if the operation is retried.
// spred_tidlig_retur implements the `?` operator: unwrap Ok or return Err from the current function.
// feil_kart transforms the error value while preserving the Ok path (like Result::map_err).
// feil_flat_kart chains fallible operations: if the first succeeds, run the next; otherwise propagate.
// typed_feil uses a type parameter to make the compiler enforce exhaustive error handling.
// sumtype_feil is an enum of possible error types, enabling pattern-matching exhaustion checking.
// utleder_feil generates From implementations to convert between error types automatically.
// gjenopprettings_strategi defines how a layer handles an error it receives from below.
// strategi_delvis_suksess returns completed portions along with the error.
// feil_budsjett is an SLO-based mechanism: track feil_rate_terskel over a budsjett_vindu.
// slo_brudd fires when budsjett_forbrukt exceeds feil_rate_terskel, signaling reliability degradation.
// foreslå_løsning provides actionable remediation steps for known error patterns.

// Primitive flow:
// feil propagering: fn les_konfig() -> Resultat<Konfig, KonfigFeil>
//   åpne_fil(sti)  ?   // KonfigFeil::Io hvis fil mangler
//   parse_toml(innhold) ?  // KonfigFeil::Parse ved syntaksfeil
//   valider(konfig) ?  // KonfigFeil::Validering hvis ugyldig
// feil_kontekst: åpne_fil(sti).kontekst("Leser konfig fra {sti}")
//   -> ved feil: Feil{ melding, kontekst: ["Leser konfig fra /etc/app.toml"], årsak: IoFeil }
// sumtype_feil: enum ApiFeil { Http(HttpFeil), Db(DbFeil), Intern(String) }
//   kall_api() -> Resultat<Data, ApiFeil>
//   match feil { ApiFeil::Http(e) -> ... | ApiFeil::Db(e) -> ... | ApiFeil::Intern(s) -> ... }
// feil_budsjett: over siste 1 time: maks 0.1% feil rate
//   feil_rate_terskel=0.001, budsjett_vindu=3600sek
//   hvis budsjett_forbrukt -> slo_brudd -> varsle on-call

// This defines advanced error handling: structured typed errors with causal chains, context
// layers, propagation operators, sum-type errors with exhaustive matching, recovery strategies,
// SLO-based error budgets, and diagnostic tooling with fix suggestions.
